Step 4.2: Configure Firewall Rules
Implement database firewall protection:

# Allow MySQL from localhost only
sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 3306 -s 127.0.0.1 -j ACCEPT
sudo iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport 3306 -j DROP

# Save rules
sudo netfilter-persistent save

# View rules
sudo iptables -L -n -v
Step 4.3: Create Systemd Service
Setup monitoring as a service:

sudo cat > /etc/systemd/system/opendam.service << 'EOF'
[Unit]
Description=OpenDAM Database Activity Monitor
After=mysql.service

[Service]
Type=simple
User=ubuntu
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /opt/opendam/bin/opendam_monitor.py
Restart=on-failure

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
EOF

sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable opendam
sudo systemctl start opendam
